[I] A system daemon for tracking what users are logged into the system

[T] ConsoleKit is a system daemon for tracking what users are logged
[T] into the system and how they interact with the computer
[T] It provides asynchronous notification via the system message bus.

[U] https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/ConsoleKit

[A] David Zeuthen <davidz@redhat.com>
[M] Gerardo Di Iorio <arete74@gmail.com>

[C] extra/development
[F] CROSS NO-LTO.gcc

[L] MIT
[V] 2.0.0
[P] X -----5---9 140.550

[D] b3c5b6737c615f220ef26f3a8179831b97032a072316c1b8f3b54b1b ConsoleKit2-2.0.0.tar.gz https://github.com/ConsoleKit2/ConsoleKit2/archive/2.0.0/

autogen=1
var_append confopt ' ' --enable-pam-module

var_append GCC_WRAPPER_INSERT ' ' "-I$root$(pkgprefix includedir libx11)"
var_append GCC_WRAPPER_INSERT ' ' "-L$root$(pkgprefix libdir libx11)"
